JOHANNESBURG – Economic Freedom Fighters (EFF) Member of Parliament (MP), Mbuyiseni Ndlozi on Monday hosted eNCA’s 'As It Happens'. Affectionately known as The People’s Bae, Ndlozi again showed why he is more than just a handsome face. Other politicians that will make their appearance on the show later this week include the African National Congress’ Pule Mabe, the Democratic Alliance (DA)’s Natasha Mazzone, the United Democratic Movement (UDM)’s Bantu Holomisa and the Inkatha Freedom Party’s Lisa van Merwe. [WATCH] #AsItHappens: Dr @MbuyiseniNdlozi speaks on violence against women. Calls for all men to "call each other out" and to never "protect abusers". Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/ebvi8eyiid [EARLIER] #AsItHappens: Dr @MbuyiseniNdlozi answers some viewer questions. First question is: "Whose interest is the #EFF serving?". Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/40NKrFDyxA [EARLIER] #AsItHappens: An eNCA viewer asks Dr @MbuyiseniNdlozi why people living with disabilities are not considered? Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/YjvyAYnLCX [EARLIER] #AsItHappens: Third question to Dr @MbuyiseniNdlozi is: Who do you think will be the beneficiary of land without expropriation between those who proposed the policy and those who will implement it? Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/5fkPSl3ZBz [EARLIER] #AsItHappens: Dr @MbuyiseniNdlozi in conversation with Peter Bruce @Bruceps. He asks him about an opinion piece that Bruce wrote stating that a tiny minority of black people want to farm. Asks him about the source he used to arrive to that conclusion. Courtesy #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/pwDZOTxPcP eNCA